O:9:"MagpieRSS":22:{s:6:"parser";i:0;s:12:"current_item";a:0:{}s:5:"items";a:3:{i:0;a:8:{s:5:"title";s:16:"Festival Friends";s:4:"link";s:49:"http://bollingtonfestival.org.uk/festival-friends";s:11:"description";s:4232:"<div class="field field--name-field-image field--type-image field--label-hidden"><div class="field__items"><div class="field__item even"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://bollingtonfestival.org.uk/sites/default/files/Friends%20Logo.png" width="4064" height="928" alt="" /></div></div></div><div class="field field--name-title field--type-ds field--label-hidden"><div class="field__items"><div class="field__item even" property="dc:title"><h1 class="page-title">Festival Friends</h1></div></div></div><div class="field field--name-field-main-text field--type-text-long field--label-hidden"><div class="field__items"><div class="field__item even"><p><strong>?The Bollington Festival enriches the lives of people who live in Bollington, regardless of age, background, interests or abilities?</strong></p>
<p>	The support of our Friends is vital in keeping this wonderful legacy going. Without it future Festivals are uncertain and their programmes restricted in vision.</p>
<p>	Since its inception in 1964, the Bollington Festival has enriched the lives of so many people who live in and around Bollington, and in 2019 it will be doing so again with your help.</p>
<p>	Each festival has been a catalyst for new events and partnerships bringing new creative activities to the community. It has developed over the years with a positive impact on village life and engendered a true community spirit.</p>
<p>	Over the last 50+ years, Bollington Festival has given birth to a Community Theatre company, Choir, Light Opera Group, Children?s Music Theatre, Chamber Concert series, prize-winning Brass Band, Sci(ence) Bar evenings and regular Jazz and Comedy night sessions within a thriving Arts Centre.</p>
<p>	<strong>So please support Bollington Festival 2019. </strong>We need to ensure funding is in place before 2019 in order to implement all the wonderful ideas the vibrant community of Bollington has suggested for its next Festival.</p>
<p>	Become a Festival Friend, and not only support the Festival in 2019, but see how you can benefit too.</p>
<h1>
	<a href="/ckfinder/userfiles/files/2019%20Friends%20Leaflet%20Back%20Page%2024_9_16.pdf" target="_blank">DOWNLOAD AN APPLICATION FORM HERE</a></h1>
<p>	 </p>
<p>	<strong>How you can become a Friend of Bollington Festival 2019 and ensure its success in the years to come...</strong></p>
<p>	<strong>___________________________________</strong></p>
<p>	<strong>Adelphi Friends: £50+</strong></p>
<ul><li>
		Selected ticket offers during the Festival</li>
<li>
		Festival brochure sent to home in advance</li>
<li>
		2 free drinks vouchers</li>
<li>
		Support recognised on Festival website</li>
<li>
		Reductions on pre-Festival events</li>
<li>
		Friends steward at Marquee events</li>
</ul><p>	<strong>_________________________________________</strong></p>
<p>	<strong>Ingersley Friends: £100+ </strong>All of the above, plus</p>
<ul><li>
		2 free Festival tickets of your choice</li>
<li>
		A further 2 free drinks vouchers (4 in total)</li>
</ul><p>	__________________________________________</p>
<p>	<strong>Clarence Friends: £250+ </strong>All of the above, plus</p>
<ul><li>
		A further 2 free Festival tickets of your choice (4 in total)</li>
<li>
		A further 2 free drinks vouchers (6 in total)</li>
</ul><p>	<strong>___________________________________</strong></p>
<p>	<strong>Bespoke Giving Friends or Corporate Sponsorship: starts at £500</strong></p>
<p>	This offers you the opportunity to play your part in ensuring that the Bollington Festival 2019 can go ahead and is a huge success.</p>
<p>	By choosing to become a Bespoke Friend you could fund an aspect of the Festival that you have a particular interest in, be it science, poetry, jazz, dance, young people... You tell us!</p>
<p>	In return we offer special tailor-made packages to meet your particular Festival requirements (for tickets, hospitality, recognition in the Festival Programme etc.) that reflect the level of your support.</p>
<p>	These will be dealt with personally by our appointed Friend of the Friends.</p>
<p>	For more information please contact<strong>: <a href="mailto:festivalfriends@bollingtonfestival.org.uk">festivalfriends@bollingtonfestival.org.uk</a></strong></p>
